BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
That first subtraction may be tricky. It may help to write that as addition of [`-1`] times the rest:

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
4-(3x-9) \amp=4+(-1)(3x-9)\\
\amp=4+\Big(-1(3x)-(-1)(9)\Big)\\
\amp=4+(-3x+9)\\
\amp=4+(9-3x)\\
\amp=4+(9+(-3x))\\
\amp=(4+9)+(-3x)\\
\amp=13+(-3x)=13-3x
\end{aligned}
```]

